F-statistic: 6.969 on 1 and 126 DF,  p-value: 0.009342

Full sep is significantly predictive of depression, but with a very small effect size (F = 6.97, p = 0.009, r-squared = 0.05). The drop in effect size between the psych sep subscale and the full sep scale suggests that the psych sep subscale is more useful as a predictive tool on its own.
